# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SIFTER AI — Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in the keys you want to use
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── OPTION A: Fully Local (no data ever leaves your machine) ──────
#
# Works with any local AI tool that has an OpenAI-compatible API:
#
#   Ollama      → localhost:11434/v1  (default)
#   LM Studio   → localhost:1234/v1
#   vLLM        → localhost:8000/v1
#
# LOCAL_AI_MODEL  = the model name your local tool uses
# LOCAL_AI_BASE_URL = the API URL (defaults to Ollama if not set)
#
# Examples:
#
#   Ollama (default):
#   LOCAL_AI_MODEL=llama3.1:8b
#
#   LM Studio:
#   LOCAL_AI_MODEL=llama-3.1-8b-instruct
#   LOCAL_AI_BASE_URL=http://localhost:1234/v1
#
#   vLLM on a company server:
#   LOCAL_AI_MODEL=meta-llama/Meta-Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct
#   LOCAL_AI_BASE_URL=http://your-server-ip:8000/v1

# LOCAL_AI_MODEL=llama3.1:8b
# LOCAL_AI_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434/v1


# ── OPTION B: Free Cloud APIs (fast, resumes anonymized in transit) ──
#
# You can set multiple keys — the app uses them all in parallel.
# Priority order: Local AI → Cerebras → Gemini → Groq
#
# Cerebras — free at https://cloud.cerebras.ai  (fastest: 2000+ tok/s)
# CEREBRAS_API_KEY=csk-...
#
# Google Gemini — free at https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
# GOOGLE_GENERATIVE_AI_API_KEY=AIza...
#
# Groq — free at https://console.groq.com
# GROQ_API_KEY=gsk_...


# ── OPTION C: Private cloud (data stays in your Azure/AWS/GCP tenant) ──
#
# Azure OpenAI:
# LOCAL_AI_MODEL=gpt-4o
# LOCAL_AI_BASE_URL=https://YOUR-RESOURCE.openai.azure.com/openai/deployments/YOUR-DEPLOYMENT
#
# AWS Bedrock / Google Vertex: contact wyatt.rantz@gmail.com for setup help
